      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHIKANIC (1) tackled a much tougher race last time in town and wasn't far away. Boasts a great record this course and distance with four wins and five minors from 10 tries. Expected to bounce back. EXONUMIA (3) speared to the lead from a wide alley before fading right out of it over 1300m at Bordertown last time. Will appreciate the firmer footing and capable of sharp improvement. BORN TO SHINE (4) doesn't boast the best winning strike rate but ran a nice race last time out, finishing fourth over 1100m at Bordertown. First try here and can run a forward race. SUMADARTSON (5) has not won for a long while. Latest was beaten 7 lengths into fifth at this track over 1100m after being up on the pace until straightening. Should be thereabouts. LORD MORTON (2) is worth including with repeat of latest.",
